  "text": "To test for swarming and motility, V. fischeri ETJB1H wild-type, flgF À and motY À strains were examined for any phenotypic changes, such as cell spreading, that leads to colony pattern differentiation. The media consisted of LBS with 0.5% (w/v) Difco bacto-agar, to which glucose (5 g L À1 ) was added as previously described [CITATION_1] . Swarm plates were inoculated from an overnight culture in LBS agar (1.5% w/v) using a sterile toothpick. Plates were then incubated at 28°C for 24 h.",
